He produced thousands of drawings and paintings in a career which won him a medal from the Royal Society for the Protection of Birds. Born in Reading, his father Gerald Gillmor was an accountant while his mother Mildred worked in antique coins. As a boy, he enjoyed school trips to locations where there were plenty of birds to draw. He met his wife Susan Norman through the Reading Guild of Artists. Once their children fled the nest, they moved to Cley in Norfolk, a perfect location to view birds on the marshes.